%BOM---------------------
Date:9/23/2011 1:05:36 AM
From:J Mako
re: if you really believe in Buffett's maxim of selling never

The way I see it, Buffett's "buy and hold forever" is a strategy he uses to
convince would-be business sellers to sell him their treasured businesses. He
wants others to see him as a white knight. He knows too well if you look at the
individual holding alone, "hold forever" is irrational. But in the overall
scheme of things, this is a "premium" he pays in order to improve his chance to
acquire high quality businesses.

