re CAT and IBM during the great depression-
IBM survived and prospered because Watson kept the factories running building
up inventory. With his huge inventory of tabulator machines IBM was able to bit
on the huge newly instated social security contract that required processing
power.
CAT was able to keep themselves afloat selling AG machines to the Soviet Union.
