CAT was able to supply them with big machines that they wanted.

Looks to me that both were more lucky then smart, or at least they know how to
grasp an opportunity under very adverse circumstances. Still CAT revenues went
from 50M$+ to 13M$+ If someone really believes that a great recession may come,
picking winners will be futile, the thing to do is so short the indices.
